He makes a tally of the number of ice creams he sells on Friday.
\newline

\begin{center}
\TallyMarks{8}{3}
\end{center}

Work out the number of ice creams he sells on Friday.
\newline

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{ccc}
Bottle $A$ & Bottle $B$ & Bottle $C$ \\
160\,ml & 200\,ml & 240\,ml \\
\$3.75 & \$4.75 & \$6.50 \\
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

_rawBody:
Antonio has a shop near the beach.

\begin{parts}
\item \begin{subparts}
\subpart He makes a tally of the number of ice creams he sells on Friday.

\begin{center}
\TallyMarks{8}{3}
\end{center}

Work out the number of ice creams he sells on Friday.

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{1}

\subpart 15 of the ice creams he sells on Friday are vanilla.

Work out the fraction of ice creams he sells on Friday that are vanilla.\\
Give your answer in its simplest form.

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{1}

\subpart He buys tubs of ice cream for his shop in the ratio vanilla : chocolate $= 11 : 7$.\\
He buys 28 tubs of chocolate ice cream.

Work out how many tubs of vanilla ice cream he buys.

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{2}

\end{subparts}

\item Antonio records the number of chairs his shop hires out on each day for a week.
\[123 \quad 98 \quad 116 \quad 45 \quad 67 \quad 165 \quad 156\]

\begin{subparts}
\subpart Work out the range.

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{1}

\subpart Find the median.

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{2}

\subpart Calculate the mean.

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{2}

\end{subparts}

\item \begin{subparts}
\subpart Antonio buys beach balls for \$2.50 each and sells them for \$4.20 each.

Work out the percentage profit he makes on each beach ball.

\AnswerLine[][\%]
\Marks{2}

\subpart A beach ball is a sphere with radius 15\,cm.

Calculate the volume of the beach ball.\\
Give the units of your answer.

[The volume, $V$, of a sphere with radius $r$ is $V = \dfrac{4}{3}\pi r^3$.]

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{3}

\end{subparts}

\item The shop sells sun cream in bottles $A$, $B$ and $C$.

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{ccc}
Bottle $A$ & Bottle $B$ & Bottle $C$ \\
160\,ml & 200\,ml & 240\,ml \\
\$3.75 & \$4.75 & \$6.50 \\
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

Work out which bottle is the best value.\\
You must show all your working.

\AnswerLine[Bottle][]
\Marks{3}

\end{parts}

